1
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Western Poland, 1932

2
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,000
INVINCIBLE

3
00:00:35,001 --> 00:00:39,001
INVINCIBLE
(based on real-life events)

4
00:02:50,065 --> 00:02:53,978
It was in a country far away.
I don't know which one.

5
00:02:54,065 --> 00:02:56,021
But it was a distant land.

6
00:02:56,022 --> 00:02:57,978
A prince lost his mind
and imagined himself...

7
00:02:58,065 --> 00:03:02,183
- ...to be a rooster.
- A rooster? Like this one?

8
00:03:02,465 --> 00:03:06,378
Yes. He took refuge
under the dining-room table...

9
00:03:06,465 --> 00:03:11,220
...striped naked, and refused
to eat anything but grain.

10
00:03:11,305 --> 00:03:14,377
- And then?
- The King called in magicians and doctors...

11
00:03:14,465 --> 00:03:18,014
...to cure his son,
but to no avail.

12
00:03:18,465 --> 00:03:22,777
One day, an unknown sage
arrived, took off his clothes...

13
00:03:22,865 --> 00:03:27,864
...and joined the prince under the table,
saying he too was a rooster.

14
00:03:28,145 --> 00:03:32,058
Eventually, the sage convinced
the prince to get dressed.

15
00:03:32,145 --> 00:03:36,058
And finally to sit down and eat
with the others. "Don't ever think"...

16
00:03:36,145 --> 00:03:38,101
...said the sage, "...that by
eating like...

17
00:03:38,102 --> 00:03:40,058
...a man, with other|men at the table...

18
00:03:40,145 --> 00:03:43,057
...a rooster ceases to
be what he is."

19
00:03:43,145 --> 00:03:45,380
"You can do anything with...

20
00:03:45,381 --> 00:03:47,616
...men in their world.
Or even for them."

21
00:03:47,705 --> 00:03:49,844
"And yet remain the
rooster that your are."

22
00:03:49,845 --> 00:03:51,983
I'm so proud of you, Benjamin.

23
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:55,978
Such young little fellow, and 
brighter than all the adults.

24
00:03:56,065 --> 00:03:58,977
Guess what?
I have some money.

25
00:03:59,265 --> 00:04:01,842
How would you like to
eat in a restaurant?

26
00:04:01,843 --> 00:04:04,419
A restaurant?
Really?

27
00:04:07,865 --> 00:04:09,381
What do you think
about her and me, huh?

28
00:04:09,465 --> 00:04:12,138
- You'd be fine.
- Yeah, it's true!

29
00:04:12,465 --> 00:04:14,643
Miss? Miss!

30
00:04:14,644 --> 00:04:16,822
She has nice tits,
and a fine ass.

31
00:04:16,945 --> 00:04:21,382
- I wouldn't say no to sleeping with her.
- Miss!

32
00:04:21,465 --> 00:04:23,301
Miss, miss!

33
00:04:25,745 --> 00:04:28,401
Hey, miss! Where the hell are
the...

34
00:04:28,402 --> 00:04:31,058
...girls in this stinking
place, huh?

35
00:04:47,305 --> 00:04:49,643
Could I have another one, please?

36
00:04:49,644 --> 00:04:51,981
Hey, fatty!
You should watch your weight.

37
00:04:52,065 --> 00:04:55,978
Or soon you'll be wider than
you're tall. Like a potato.

38
00:04:56,065 --> 00:04:58,977
Like a stuffed pig!

39
00:04:59,265 --> 00:05:02,177
Hey, fatty!
What's your name?

40
00:05:02,665 --> 00:05:06,943
He's not fat!
He's my brother and he's strong.

41
00:05:07,065 --> 00:05:11,900
I'm a blacksmith. My name
is Zishe. Zishe Breitbart.

42
00:05:16,385 --> 00:05:19,457
Hey, fatty!
I'm talking to you.

43
00:05:20,145 --> 00:05:23,296
Our fatty is a jew.

44
00:05:23,385 --> 00:05:26,297
A big fat jew.

45
00:05:26,385 --> 00:05:29,218
A fat one, and a thin one.

46
00:05:30,305 --> 00:05:34,218
The fat jew eats too much,
and the thin jew not enough.

47
00:05:34,305 --> 00:05:37,103
Hey, fatty! Why doesn't...

48
00:05:37,104 --> 00:05:39,902
...the little one
eat anything, huh?

49
00:05:39,985 --> 00:05:41,964
You should eat more,
like your fat brother.

50
00:05:41,965 --> 00:05:43,944
Good idea.

51
00:05:44,025 --> 00:05:46,983
You're too thin.

52
00:05:47,465 --> 00:05:51,663
- The thick and the thin...
- ...together through thick and thin.

53
00:05:57,145 --> 00:06:00,262
- Open your mouth!
- And eat!

54
00:06:12,705 --> 00:06:14,661
Hey!

55
00:06:16,065 --> 00:06:18,021
Hey!

56
00:06:26,545 --> 00:06:28,803
You will pay me for this!
Have you an idea...

57
00:06:28,804 --> 00:06:31,061
... how much beer that was?
One hectolitre.

58
00:06:31,385 --> 00:06:35,298
And do you know how much a barrel costs?
And how much that table costs?

59
00:06:35,385 --> 00:06:37,580
It wasn't his fault,
the others started it!

60
00:06:37,581 --> 00:06:39,776
As for the money,
I'd like to pay.

61
00:06:39,865 --> 00:06:43,778
Yes, we'd really like to pay for
this, but we don't have any money.

62
00:06:43,865 --> 00:06:46,123
What I should do
is call the police.

63
00:06:46,124 --> 00:06:48,381
But I think there's a way
for you to pay for the damage.

64
00:06:48,465 --> 00:06:52,378
The circus is in town.
Outside, by the gate.

65
00:06:52,465 --> 00:06:56,378
There's a famous "strongman".
And there's prize money to be won...

66
00:06:56,465 --> 00:06:58,535
...for the man who can beat him!

67
00:07:59,545 --> 00:08:04,141
Ladies and Gentlemen,
dear children!

68
00:08:04,225 --> 00:08:09,157
I would like to announce that our
Hercules has a challenger!

69
00:08:09,945 --> 00:08:12,681
A strong young man, without doubt.

70
00:08:12,682 --> 00:08:15,417
But in more than 20 years...

71
00:08:15,625 --> 00:08:19,015
...our Hercules,
our Colossus of Rhodes...

72
00:08:19,785 --> 00:08:22,982
...has never been defeated.

73
00:08:29,345 --> 00:08:32,977
For years we have been
raising the prize...

74
00:08:33,785 --> 00:08:37,494
...to the amount of 5.000 Zloty
for any man...

75
00:08:38,665 --> 00:08:43,216
...who proves himself stronger.
Not without reason...

76
00:08:43,305 --> 00:08:47,776
...the ancients have proclaimed
the Colossus of Rhodes...

77
00:08:47,865 --> 00:08:52,222
...one of the 7
Wonders of the World!

78
00:09:13,865 --> 00:09:16,760
And now, highly esteemed audience...

79
00:09:16,761 --> 00:09:19,656
...his challenger this evening:

80
00:09:20,265 --> 00:09:23,974
Zishe Breitbart!
Blacksmith from this town.

81
00:11:22,865 --> 00:11:25,937
I can do more!
I can do more!

82
00:12:01,465 --> 00:12:05,378
Yitzak, come! There's a visitor.
A real gentleman.

83
00:12:05,465 --> 00:12:09,458
- What does he want?
- I don't know. He arrived in a motorcar.

84
00:12:09,545 --> 00:12:14,300
And, oh my God, I have
nothing to offer him.

85
00:12:26,785 --> 00:12:29,777
Landwehr. Alfred Landwehr.

86
00:12:29,865 --> 00:12:32,760
Pleased to meet you,
Mr. Breitbart.

87
00:12:32,761 --> 00:12:35,656
And this is your strong son.

88
00:12:37,625 --> 00:12:40,583
- Please! Sit down!
- Thank you.

89
00:12:46,905 --> 00:12:49,339
I'm an agent for variety artists.

90
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:51,774
Dancers, chucklers, magicians.

91
00:12:51,865 --> 00:12:56,541
Everything that is in demand.
And the demand in Berlin is enormous.

92
00:12:56,625 --> 00:12:59,600
I possess an instinct for
great talents.

93
00:12:59,601 --> 00:13:02,575
For people who will go
straight to the top.

94
00:13:02,665 --> 00:13:06,578
I was at the circus yesterday to
see the local strongman, when your son--

95
00:13:06,665 --> 00:13:08,621
You need not go on.
We are respectable people.

96
00:13:08,622 --> 00:13:10,578
For a jew this is not
the right thing.

97
00:13:10,665 --> 00:13:14,453
But the most gifted people
in cinema, in theatre and art are.

98
00:13:14,545 --> 00:13:18,982
I never even thought about leaving.
I belong in this smithy...

99
00:13:19,065 --> 00:13:23,581
- ...in our little Shtetl.
- You see, our jewish Shtetls...

100
00:13:23,665 --> 00:13:25,725
...are like holy
books, open...

101
00:13:25,726 --> 00:13:28,785
...to the eyes of God. And the
Day of the Torment...

102
00:13:28,865 --> 00:13:31,823
...even the fish tremble
in the brook.

103
00:13:31,945 --> 00:13:36,780
In spring, during Passover,
the trees rejoice.

104
00:13:37,065 --> 00:13:40,978
Sir... you're like a shopkeeper,
with empty shelves.

105
00:13:41,065 --> 00:13:43,262
With nothing to sell.

106
00:13:46,465 --> 00:13:49,935
Son... you'll have
to attend university!

107
00:13:51,705 --> 00:13:53,280
You've said that beautifully...

108
00:13:53,281 --> 00:13:54,856
...really.

109
00:13:55,225 --> 00:13:58,217
Do you know how old the
boy is? 9!

110
00:13:59,545 --> 00:14:02,440
This little fellow
is just 9 years old.

111
00:14:02,441 --> 00:14:05,336
And to think that this
is my brother, Benjamin.

112
00:14:06,065 --> 00:14:09,139
Look at what an incredible
boy my brother is.

113
00:14:16,545 --> 00:14:20,458
Good morning, ladies and gentlemen.
Are you all right?

114
00:14:20,545 --> 00:14:23,503
- Yes, thank you.
- Fine! Me too.

115
00:14:28,305 --> 00:14:32,378
Good morning, Mr. Landwehr!
We've just been talking about you.

116
00:14:32,465 --> 00:14:35,042
Did you sleep in the motorcar?

117
00:14:35,043 --> 00:14:37,619
There isn't even a hotel
around here to spend the night.

118
00:14:37,705 --> 00:14:42,493
- Good morning. Mornin'. Mornin'.
- You are an exceptional man.

119
00:14:42,865 --> 00:14:45,083
I am, when i'm after
an exceptional talent.

120
00:14:45,084 --> 00:14:47,302
Zishe, listen!

121
00:14:47,385 --> 00:14:50,121
I want you to come with
me just for the day!

122
00:14:50,122 --> 00:14:52,157
I have something to show you.

123
00:14:52,945 --> 00:14:57,063
- But i can't leave. I must work.
- Your father...

124
00:14:57,145 --> 00:14:59,101
...would excuse you
for an afternoon, huh?

125
00:14:59,102 --> 00:15:01,058
My son is able to make up his
own mind...

126
00:15:01,059 --> 00:15:02,624
...about such things.

127
00:15:02,625 --> 00:15:05,103
You'll be most interested to see
what i'm going to show you.

128
00:15:39,785 --> 00:15:42,760
Look Zishe, look
at all the motorcars!

129
00:15:42,761 --> 00:15:45,735
There must be every motorcar
in the whole world...

130
00:15:46,065 --> 00:15:47,902
...right in Berlin!

131
00:15:47,903 --> 00:15:49,740
More than motorcars, young man.
Watch what's coming.

132
00:15:54,705 --> 00:15:57,618
That's a flying machine!
I've read about it.

133
00:16:03,085 --> 00:16:06,443
Look at how many
people it can carry.

134
00:16:07,385 --> 00:16:11,298
Aeroplanes will never compete
against that.

135
00:16:34,145 --> 00:16:36,101
Benjamin!

136
00:16:37,545 --> 00:16:40,537
- Benjamin, wake up!
- I am awake!

137
00:16:42,065 --> 00:16:45,137
- I've been thinking.
- So have I.

138
00:16:50,265 --> 00:16:53,120
Do you believe God gives to
each of us a gift?

139
00:16:53,121 --> 00:16:55,976
Of course.

140
00:16:56,265 --> 00:16:58,984
God made me strong,
Benjamin. Don't you think...

141
00:16:58,985 --> 00:17:01,703
...that he made me strong
for a reason?

142
00:17:01,785 --> 00:17:06,620
A blacksmith needs to be strong.

143
00:17:06,705 --> 00:17:11,460
But I am stronger than a
blacksmith needs to be.

144
00:17:11,945 --> 00:17:16,621
Sometimes we don't understand
why God does what He does.

145
00:17:20,465 --> 00:17:23,537
This is what I must find out.

146
00:17:27,265 --> 00:17:29,904
- Zishe?
- What? Tell me.

147
00:17:31,865 --> 00:17:35,744
The Book of Prophets says:
"Spare me...

148
00:17:35,865 --> 00:17:39,744
...that i may recover strength,
before i go hence...

149
00:17:40,705 --> 00:17:43,936
...and be no more.
And be no more."

150
00:18:00,545 --> 00:18:02,501
- And?
- And, what?

151
00:18:03,065 --> 00:18:05,977
- What do you think about it?
- About what?

152
00:18:06,065 --> 00:18:08,004
Berlin.

153
00:18:08,005 --> 00:18:09,944
Let me talk to the
Rabbi first.

154
00:18:10,465 --> 00:18:14,378
But before anything, we have to
celebrate Passover.

155
00:18:14,465 --> 00:18:15,821
But...

156
00:18:18,985 --> 00:18:21,220
Children, when we fled Egypt,
we didn't...

157
00:18:21,221 --> 00:18:23,456
...have time for the
bread to rise.

158
00:18:23,545 --> 00:18:27,458
Hannah? What happened
when we came to the sea?

159
00:18:27,545 --> 00:18:30,901
- Hashem opened the seas.
- Yes, he did!

160
00:18:32,385 --> 00:18:34,841
And, Raffael? How many
years did we stay in the desert?

161
00:18:35,292 --> 00:18:36,328
Forty.

162
00:18:36,385 --> 00:18:39,343
Yes. All right.

163
00:18:39,785 --> 00:18:42,822
- Search for it!
- Yes!

164
00:18:55,705 --> 00:18:57,661
Where is it?

165
00:19:04,065 --> 00:19:06,977
It must be somewhere.

166
00:19:09,665 --> 00:19:13,214
Maybe under the pillow.
Hannele found it!

167
00:19:13,305 --> 00:19:16,217
- Wonderful!
- Hannele found it!

168
00:19:16,305 --> 00:19:19,775
- She has found it.
- Very well!

169
00:19:19,865 --> 00:19:21,821
Wonderful!

170
00:19:23,065 --> 00:19:25,977
- How much do you want for it?
- 6 Zloty.

171
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:30,583
No, that's too much!

172
00:19:30,665 --> 00:19:32,439
Yes...

173
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:34,214
- 6!
- Yes.

174
00:19:34,465 --> 00:19:38,981
I want to thank the Allmighty
for my good wife, and my children.

175
00:19:39,065 --> 00:19:43,661
You are the salt of earth.
And you fill my heart with joy.

176
00:19:44,865 --> 00:19:47,959
Today, I want to thank
God in particular...

177
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:51,054
...for my strong firstborn.

178
00:19:51,545 --> 00:19:55,663
Zishe, my son! You will
go out into the World...

179
00:19:55,985 --> 00:19:58,977
...but don't ever forget
who you are!

180
00:21:07,545 --> 00:21:10,503
Hold on! Hold on!

181
00:21:37,665 --> 00:21:41,783
I've travelled very far. I've been as
far as Vilna. But a thing like this...

182
00:21:41,865 --> 00:21:43,821
...a thing like this i've
never seen before.

183
00:21:43,822 --> 00:21:45,778
Can you give me a ride?

184
00:21:45,865 --> 00:21:50,620
- Where can we take you?
- You're not going to Berlin, by any chance?

185
00:22:00,065 --> 00:22:02,977
- Are you hungry?
- All the time.

186
00:22:03,065 --> 00:22:05,977
My mother has never been
able to feed me enough.

187
00:22:06,065 --> 00:22:10,263
And you want to walk
all the way to Berlin?

188
00:22:11,065 --> 00:22:15,616
Yes. I have a ticket for
the train, first class.

189
00:22:15,705 --> 00:22:20,679
But i'm going to return the ticket, and
my mother will get a new dress instead.

190
00:22:20,865 --> 00:22:24,778
I've heard there are
many pretty girls in Berlin.

191
00:22:24,865 --> 00:22:29,222
Girls like you won't find in
the country. Maybe you'll meet one.

192
00:22:29,305 --> 00:22:32,854
I have already, sort of.
In a dream.

193
00:22:34,225 --> 00:22:38,138
But I couldn't see her face, because...
I know it sounds strange...

194
00:22:38,225 --> 00:22:43,140
...but there was so much light.
I think she was a princess.

195
00:23:17,145 --> 00:23:21,058
You didn't come specially for me?
How did you know?

196
00:23:21,145 --> 00:23:23,722
Your reputation is
faster than your feet.

197
00:23:23,723 --> 00:23:26,299
My name is Delilah.

198
00:23:27,065 --> 00:23:30,023
Better take care, Samson!

199
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:59,300
Berlin, May 1932

200
00:24:58,865 --> 00:25:01,982
It's me, Zishe!
Zishe Breitbart!

201
00:25:03,625 --> 00:25:07,095
You want to talk to Mr. Landwehr?

202
00:25:07,185 --> 00:25:10,780
Are you still there?
Hello? Hello?

203
00:25:11,065 --> 00:25:14,823
- Speak please.
- What?

204
00:25:16,065 --> 00:25:18,977
- Please speak.
- Yes!

205
00:25:19,065 --> 00:25:21,977
- Where are you?
- In Berlin.

206
00:25:22,065 --> 00:25:24,080
Come and see us at once.
Mr. Landwehr...

207
00:25:24,081 --> 00:25:27,095
...is expecting you. We
thought you were lost.

208
00:25:32,665 --> 00:25:34,896
A girl you say.

209
00:25:35,065 --> 00:25:37,021
And she wanted to marry
you at once?

210
00:25:37,022 --> 00:25:38,978
Well, actually no.

211
00:25:39,065 --> 00:25:41,204
She just wanted to keep me.

212
00:25:41,205 --> 00:25:43,343
Don't just stand there,
have a seat.

213
00:25:43,425 --> 00:25:45,381
Thank you.

214
00:25:49,265 --> 00:25:53,781
You realize, that the possibilities
to employ you are...

215
00:25:53,865 --> 00:25:57,494
- ...somewhat limited.
- Yes? What do you mean by that?

216
00:25:58,545 --> 00:26:01,821
No, no, don't be afraid!

217
00:26:02,865 --> 00:26:07,859
I'm good at the work i do.
The best, if i may say so.

218
00:26:09,385 --> 00:26:13,776
I'm going to employ you in an
establishment called...

219
00:26:13,865 --> 00:26:16,857
..."Hanussen's Palace
of the Occult".

220
00:26:18,065 --> 00:26:21,978
I don't quite understand.
What am i supposed to do there?

221
00:26:22,065 --> 00:26:26,377
I've talked to Hanussen, and he
was immediately pleased with my idea.

222
00:26:26,465 --> 00:26:30,378
Hanussen has understood something
about the insecurity of our times.

223
00:26:30,465 --> 00:26:32,723
Inflation, unemployment,
mass strikes...

224
00:26:32,724 --> 00:26:34,981
...attempted coups, bank rushes.

225
00:26:35,065 --> 00:26:38,978
People long for a
strong man, a leader.

226
00:26:39,065 --> 00:26:42,978
And Hanussen is the clairvoyant,
the prophet of this longing.

227
00:26:43,065 --> 00:26:45,977
And what does that have
to do with me?

228
00:26:46,785 --> 00:26:51,703
I can tell you! You will be
a kind of contrasting program:

229
00:26:52,385 --> 00:26:55,041
The strenght of the body,
against the...

230
00:26:55,042 --> 00:26:57,698
...dark powers of the
spirit of the occult.

231
00:26:57,785 --> 00:27:00,861
And i have to point out to you
right now that you...

232
00:27:00,862 --> 00:27:03,337
...must play a certain game.

233
00:27:03,425 --> 00:27:06,701
I can't do that.
I'm strong, that's all.

234
00:27:06,785 --> 00:27:11,743
I don't demand anything else from you.
And furthermore, you'll keep your mouth shut!

235
00:27:12,225 --> 00:27:15,058
I'll meet with tomorrow
at Hanussen's.

236
00:27:16,465 --> 00:27:18,615
Dismissed!

237
00:27:18,905 --> 00:27:23,905
PALACE OF THE OCCULT

238
00:27:29,945 --> 00:27:31,901
No, impossible!

