00:54:57,800 --> 00:55:00,800
And it's mine.

491
00:55:00,900 --> 00:55:02,900
All mine.

492
00:55:31,000 --> 00:55:33,000
EXIT

493
00:55:56,800 --> 00:56:00,700
I didn't want to disturb you.
I'm sorry.

494
00:56:00,800 --> 00:56:03,900
You're not disturbing me at all.
Please, stay.

495
00:56:04,000 --> 00:56:07,100
That was really won--
Wonderful.

496
00:56:08,100 --> 00:56:11,400
Why don't you sit
down next to me?

497
00:56:47,400 --> 00:56:51,900
I don't know anything about music.
Tell me, where did you learn all this?

498
00:56:52,000 --> 00:56:56,600
I thought you were a princess when
I first heard you play. Tell me.

499
00:56:56,700 --> 00:56:59,300
I studied at the Conservatory,
in Prague.

500
00:56:59,301 --> 00:57:01,900
You see, i had high hopes then.

501
00:57:02,000 --> 00:57:04,650
And i've never really
given them up.

502
00:57:04,651 --> 00:57:07,300
And why are you here?

503
00:57:07,400 --> 00:57:09,550
The reason is that
i'm a stateless person.

504
00:57:09,551 --> 00:57:11,800
Do you know what that means?

505
00:57:11,801 --> 00:57:15,700
As a child they kept pushing
me around between three countries.

506
00:57:15,800 --> 00:57:20,300
I never knew my parents.
And when Hanussen was in Prague...

507
00:57:20,400 --> 00:57:23,500
- ...he took me away with him.
- He was in Prague?

508
00:57:23,501 --> 00:57:28,200
Yes, in Prague. And he gave me
work with his Palace Orchestra.

509
00:57:28,300 --> 00:57:32,200
I'm sure you have noticed that
he doesn't treat me well.

510
00:57:32,300 --> 00:57:35,600
Ye. Yes, i've noticed that.

511
00:57:36,300 --> 00:57:39,900
But i stay with him all the same.
Well, yes.

512
00:57:41,500 --> 00:57:44,400
Why am i still with him?

513
00:57:45,700 --> 00:57:49,300
Miss Marta, I want you to...
I am...

514
00:57:49,400 --> 00:57:52,400
Zishe, I know what you mean.

515
00:57:53,800 --> 00:57:58,000
Your music...
It's so beautiful when you play.

516
00:57:59,000 --> 00:58:03,200
- You see, I have a dream.
- Can you tell me what it is?

517
00:58:03,300 --> 00:58:07,200
Someday I'd like to play
Beethoven's Third Piano Concerto.

518
00:58:07,300 --> 00:58:09,800
With a full orchestra
to accompany me.

519
00:58:09,801 --> 00:58:12,300
I would give anything for that.

520
00:58:14,500 --> 00:58:17,600
I have a vision deep inside.

521
00:58:18,000 --> 00:58:22,400
Come with me.
I'll show you.